"```sql\nSELECT AVG(vote_count) \nFROM (\n    SELECT COUNT(votes.PostId) AS vote_count\n    FROM votes\n    JOIN users ON votes.UserId = users.Id\n    WHERE users.Age = (SELECT MAX(Age) FROM users)\n    GROUP BY users.Id\n) AS user_vote_counts;\n```\n\nThis SQL query calculates the average number of posts voted by the oldest users. It first finds the maximum age from the users table to identify the oldest users. Then, it counts the number of posts each of these users has voted on and calculates the average of these counts."